#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs0.5"
msgid "36. Dutiyapavāraṇāsikkhāpada"
msgstr "The second training rule on satisfaction"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.84"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.36.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.332"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa784"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa "
"ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena dve bhikkhū kosalesu janapade sāvatthiṃ "
"addhānamaggappaṭipannā honti."
msgstr ""
"At that time two monks were traveling on a main road through the Kosalan "
"country on their way to Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs1.3"
msgid "Eko bhikkhu anācāraṃ ācarati."
msgstr "One monk misbehaved,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs1.4"
msgid "Dutiyo bhikkhu taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and the second monk said to him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs1.5"
msgid "“māvuso, evarūpamakāsi, netaṃ kappatī”ti."
msgstr "“Don’t do that; it’s not allowable.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs1.6"
msgid "So tasmiṃ upanandhi."
msgstr "Because of that the first monk became resentful."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs1.7"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū sāvatthiṃ agamaṃsu."
msgstr "They then carried on to Sāvatthī."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs1.8"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena sāvatthiyaṃ aññatarassa pūgassa saṃghabhattaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"Soon afterwards an association in Sāvatthī was offering a meal to the Order."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs1.9"
msgid "Dutiyo bhikkhu bhuttāvī pavārito hoti."
msgstr "When the second monk had eaten and expressed his satisfaction,"

#. VAR: Upanaddho → upanandho (si, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs1.10"
msgid ""
"Upanaddho bhikkhu ñātikulaṃ gantvā piṇḍapātaṃ ādāya yena so bhikkhu "
"tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "the resentful monk went to his family and got some almsfood."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs1.11"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "He then went to the other and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs1.12"
msgid "“bhuñjāhi, āvuso”ti."
msgstr "“Please eat!”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs1.13"
msgid "“Alaṃ, āvuso, paripuṇṇomhī”ti."
msgstr "“There’s no need; I’m full.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs1.14"
msgid "“Sundaro, āvuso, piṇḍapāto, bhuñjāhī”ti."
msgstr "“The almsfood is nice, please eat.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs1.15"
msgid "Atha kho so bhikkhu tena bhikkhunā nippīḷiyamāno taṃ piṇḍapātaṃ bhuñji."
msgstr "And because he was pressured, he ate the almsfood."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs1.16"
msgid "Upanaddho bhikkhu taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "The resentful  monk then said to him,"

#. VAR: tvampi → tvaṃ hi (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs1.17"
msgid ""
"“tvampi nāma, āvuso, maṃ vattabbaṃ maññasi yaṃ tvaṃ bhuttāvī pavārito "
"anatirittaṃ bhojanaṃ bhuñjasī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Who are you to correct me when you eat food that’s not leftover after "
"having finished your meal and expressed your satisfaction?”"

#. </p><p>
#. That is, why did he not say that the food was not leftover.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs1.18"
msgid "“Nanu, āvuso, ācikkhitabban”ti."
msgstr "“Shouldn’t you have told me?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs1.19"
msgid "“Nanu, āvuso, pucchitabban”ti."
msgstr "“Shouldn’t you have asked?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa785"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs1.20"
msgid "Atha kho so bhikkhu bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi."
msgstr "The second monk told the monks what had happened,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs1.21"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs1.22"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized the other monk,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs1.23"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ bhuttāviṃ pavāritaṃ anatirittena bhojanena "
"abhihaṭṭhuṃ pavāressatī”ti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"“How can a monk invite another monk who has finished eating and who has "
"expressed his satisfaction to eat food that’s not leftover?” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs1.24"
msgid ""
"“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, bhikkhu, bhikkhuṃ bhuttāviṃ pavāritaṃ anatirittena "
"bhojanena abhihaṭṭhuṃ pavāresī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monk, that you did this?”"

#. </p><p><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.333"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs1.25"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs1.26"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked him, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs1.27"
msgid ""
"kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, bhikkhuṃ bhuttāviṃ pavāritaṃ anatirittena "
"bhojanena abhihaṭṭhuṃ pavāressasi."
msgstr ""
"Foolish man, how can you invite another monk who has finished eating and who "
"has expressed his satisfaction to eat food that’s not leftover?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs1.28"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs1.29"
msgid "evañca pana bhikkhave imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs1.29a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa786"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs1.30"
msgid ""
"“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ bhuttāviṃ pavāritaṃ anatirittena khādanīyena vā "
"bhojanīyena vā abhihaṭṭhuṃ pavāreyya—‘handa, bhikkhu, khāda vā bhuñja vā’ti, "
"jānaṃ āsādanāpekkho, bhuttasmiṃ, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk invites another monk, whom he knows has eaten and expressed his "
"satisfaction, to eats staple or non-staple food which is not left over, "
"saying, “Here, monk, eat,” aiming to criticize him, he commits an offense "
"entailing confession.’”"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs1.31"
msgid "(<em>36</em>:<strong>85</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-pc.36.2"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.36.2.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa787"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. </span>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.1.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr ""
"… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order "
"through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is "
"unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa788"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.1.6"
msgid "Bhikkhunti"
msgstr "Another monk:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.1.7"
msgid "aññaṃ bhikkhuṃ."
msgstr "a different monk."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa789"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.1.8"
msgid "Bhuttāvī nāma"
msgstr "Who has eaten:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.1.9"
msgid ""
"pañcannaṃ bhojanānaṃ aññataraṃ bhojanaṃ, antamaso kusaggenapi bhuttaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"who has eaten any of the five staple foods, even just what fits on the tip "
"of a blade of grass."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa790"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.1.10"
msgid "Pavārito nāma"
msgstr "Expressed his satisfaction:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.1.11"
msgid ""
"asanaṃ paññāyati, bhojanaṃ paññāyati, hatthapāse ṭhito abhiharati, "
"paṭikkhepo paññāyati."
msgstr ""
"there is eating; there is staple food; it is offered by one standing within "
"arm’s reach; there is a refusal."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa791"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.1.12"
msgid "Anatirittaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Not left over:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
#. <i lang="pli">Akappiyakataṃ hoti</i>, literally, “It is done with what is not allowable.” The “it,” both here and below, refers to the ceremony of making it allowable, and the “what” refers to the food.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.1.13"
msgid "akappiyakataṃ hoti,"
msgstr "the making it leftover is done with food that is not allowable;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.1.14"
msgid "appaṭiggahitakataṃ hoti,"
msgstr "it is done with food that has not been received;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.1.15"
msgid "anuccāritakataṃ hoti,"
msgstr "it is done with food that is not held in hand;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.1.16"
msgid "ahatthapāse kataṃ hoti,"
msgstr "it is done by one who is not within arm’s reach;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.1.17"
msgid "abhuttāvinā kataṃ hoti,"
msgstr "it is done by one who has not finished eating;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.1.18"
msgid "bhuttāvinā pavāritena āsanā vuṭṭhitena kataṃ hoti,"
msgstr ""
"it is done by one who has finished eating, who has expressed his "
"satisfaction, but who has risen from his seat;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.1.19"
msgid "“alametaṃ sabban”ti avuttaṃ hoti,"
msgstr "“I’ve had enough of all of this,” has not been said;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.1.20"
msgid "na gilānātirittaṃ hoti—"
msgstr "it is not leftover from one who is sick—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.1.21"
msgid "etaṃ anatirittaṃ nāma."
msgstr "this is called “not leftover.”"

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa792"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.1.22"
msgid "Khādanīyaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Non-staple food:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.1.23"
msgid ""
"pañca bhojanāni—yāmakālikaṃ sattāhakālikaṃ yāvajīvikaṃ ṭhapetvā avasesaṃ "
"khādanīyaṃ nāma."
msgstr ""
"apart from the five staple foods, the post-midday tonics, the seven-day "
"tonics, and the lifetime tonics—the rest is called “non-staple food.”"

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa793"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.1.24"
msgid "Bhojanīyaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Staple foods:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.1.25"
msgid "pañca bhojanāni—"
msgstr "there are five kinds of staple food:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.1.26"
msgid "odano, kummāso, sattu, maccho, maṃsaṃ."
msgstr "cooked grain, porridge, flour, fish, and meat."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa794"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.1.27"
msgid "Abhihaṭṭhuṃ pavāreyyāti"
msgstr "Invites:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.1.28"
msgid "yāvatakaṃ icchasi tāvatakaṃ gaṇhāhīti."
msgstr "saying, “Take as much as you like.”"

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa795"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.1.29"
msgid "Jānāti nāma"
msgstr "He knows:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
#. The last of these three ways of knowing presumably refers to the other monk having told him directly. See discussion in note to Relinquishment 30, <ref>MS.1.2425</ref>.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.1.30"
msgid "sāmaṃ vā jānāti, aññe vā tassa ārocenti, so vā āroceti."
msgstr "he knows by himself or others have told him or the monk has told him."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa796"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.1.31"
msgid "Āsādanāpekkhoti"
msgstr "Aiming to criticize him:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.1.32"
msgid ""
"“iminā imaṃ codessāmi sāressāmi paṭicodessāmi paṭisāressāmi maṅkuṃ karissāmī”"
"ti abhiharati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"if he offers it to him, thinking, “With this I’ll accuse him/remind him"
"/counter-accuse him/counter-remind him/humiliate him,” he commits an offense "
"of wrong conduct."

#. </span>
#. </p><hr><p><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.334"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.1.33"
msgid ""
"Tassa vacanena “khādissāmi bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If, because of what he says, the other monk receives it with the intention "
"of eating it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.1.34"
msgid "Ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "For every mouthful, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.1.35"
msgid "Bhojanapariyosāne āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"When the other monk has finished eating, he commits an offense entailing "
"confession."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.85"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.36.2.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa797"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.2.1"
msgid ""
"Pavārite pavāritasaññī anatirittena khādanīyena vā bhojanīyena vā "
"abhihaṭṭhuṃ pavāreti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If the other monk has expressed his satisfaction, and he perceives that he "
"has, and he invites him to eat staple or non-staple food which is not "
"leftover, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.2.2"
msgid ""
"Pavārite vematiko anatirittena khādanīyena vā bhojanīyena vā abhihaṭṭhuṃ "
"pavāreti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If the other monk has expressed his satisfaction, but he is unsure if he "
"has, and he invites him to eat staple or non-staple food which is not "
"leftover, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.2.3"
msgid ""
"Pavārite appavāritasaññī anatirittena khādanīyena vā bhojanīyena vā "
"abhihaṭṭhuṃ pavāreti, anāpatti."
msgstr ""
"If the other monk has expressed his satisfaction, but he perceives that he "
"has not, and he invites him to eat staple or non-staple food which is not "
"leftover, there is no offense."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.2.4"
msgid ""
"Yāmakālikaṃ sattāhakālikaṃ yāvajīvikaṃ āhāratthāya abhiharati, āpatti "
"dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If he invites him to eat post-midday tonics, seven-day tonics, or lifetime "
"tonics for the purpose of food, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.2.5"
msgid ""
"Tassa vacanena “khādissāmi bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If, because of what he says, the other monk receives it with the intention "
"of eating it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.2.6"
msgid "Ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "For every mouthful, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.2.7"
msgid "Appavārite pavāritasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If the other monk has not expressed his satisfaction,  but he perceives that "
"he has, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.2.8"
msgid "Appavārite vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If the other monk has not expressed his satisfaction, but he is unsure of "
"it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.2.9"
msgid "Appavārite appavāritasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr ""
"If the other monk has not expressed his satisfaction, and he perceives that "
"he has not, there is no offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.36.2.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa798"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.3.2"
msgid "atirittaṃ kārāpetvā deti,"
msgstr "if he gives it after getting it made leftover;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.3.3"
msgid "“atirittaṃ kārāpetvā bhuñjāhī”ti deti,"
msgstr "if he gives it, saying, “Get it made leftover and then eat it;”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.3.4"
msgid "aññassatthāya haranto gacchāhīti deti,"
msgstr ""
"if he gives it, saying, “Take this food for the benefit of someone else;”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.3.5"
msgid "gilānassa sesakaṃ deti,"
msgstr "if he gives the leftovers from a sick person;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.3.6"
msgid ""
"“yāmakālikaṃ sattāhakālikaṃ yāvajīvikaṃ sati paccaye paribhuñjā”ti deti,"
msgstr ""
"if he gives, saying, “When there’s a reason, make use of these post-midday "
"tonics/seven-day tonics/lifetime tonics;”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.3.7"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.3.8"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="16"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa799"></a>
#. VAR: Dutiyapavāraṇāsikkhāpadaṃ → dutiya­pavāra­ṇa­sikkhā­padaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc36:pts-cs2.3.9"
msgid "Dutiyapavāraṇāsikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr "The sixth rule, the second training rule on satisfaction, is finished."

